dct_title_s: Sketch map of the countries referred to in the Zeno narrative
dct_description_sm: Map identifies European and North American landmasses with those from Zeno Map, of doubtful authenticity, published in 1558. Modern place names are shown. Zeno's names shown parenthetically. Includes inset of Færoe Islands (also labeled Frislanda) and Shetland Islands (also labeled Eslanda) in relation to British Isles, Norway, and Denmark. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 43 (1873), pp. 156-206; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v. 43 1873
